				<div>The same exact thing that drives the 5% failure rate on trivial combines is exactly what drives the 40% failure rate for items that triv well above what your skill can possibly reach...</div><div> </div><div>I have seen no evidence of the so called 1% per 40 points better over trivial meaning that once you are 200 pts above trivial you would have a no fail combine...IT IS NOT TRUE...a 250 GM Blacksmith can and HAS failed at making a metal bit...</div><div> </div><div>The 5% failure rate on trivial combines is based on the formual and the law of averages...</div><div> </div><div>Same goes for the 40% failure rate on GM DoN items...it is not guaranteed, it is just the formula mathmatically has a 40% chance to fail...the RNG will always play havoc with the law of averages... </div>
				
